{"id":68,"date":"2019-12-23T15:11:49","date_gmt":"2019-12-23T15:11:49","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.incoproip.com\/?post_type=industry&#038;p=68"},"modified":"2022-03-11T14:16:46","modified_gmt":"2022-03-11T14:16:46","slug":"sports-media-entertainment","status":"publish","type":"industry","link":"https:\/\/www.incoproip.com\/industries\/sports-media-entertainment\/","title":{"rendered":"Sports, Media &#038; Entertainment"},"content":{"rendered":"<section class=\"industry-jumbotron\">\n    <div class=\"jumbotron__img\">\n        <img\n            srcset=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/rise-of-underdogs-banner1920x620-576x0-c-default.jpg\"\n            src=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/rise-of-underdogs-banner1920x620-48x0-c-default.jpg\"\n            data-sizes=\"auto\"\n            data-srcset=\"\n              \/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/rise-of-underdogs-banner1920x620-576x0-c-default.jpg 576w,\n              \/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/rise-of-underdogs-banner1920x620-992x0-c-default.jpg 992w,\n              \/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/rise-of-underdogs-banner1920x620-1200x0-c-default.jpg 1200w,\n              \/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/rise-of-underdogs-banner1920x620-1920x0-c-default.jpg 1920w\"\n            data-src=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/rise-of-underdogs-banner1920x620-1920x0-c-default.jpg\"\n            alt=\"Rise&#x20;of&#x20;the&#x20;underdogs&#x20;-&#x20;how&#x20;unexpected&#x20;performances&#x20;are&#x20;affecting&#x20;the&#x20;counterfeit&#x20;market\"\n            class=\"lazyload blur-up\" \/>\n        <div class=\"jumbotron__overlay\">&nbsp;<\/div>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"container\">\n        <h2>It is estimated that the sport industry loses approximately <span>\u20ac500 million<\/span><\/h2>\n        <p>in the EU alone every year. <br \/>\r\n<br \/>\r\nSports, media &amp; entertainment are massive targets for counterfeiters. They look to capitalize on pop culture and seasonal events to exploit spikes in popularity and flog their illegitimate products.<br \/>\r\n<br \/>\r\nHowever, there is also a flipside for these sectors that a lot of those who infringe on their IP are not acting maliciously, but rather are fans of a specific sports team or character within a TV series or movie. For these instances, it requires someone enforcing on your behalf who has the knowledge and expertise to understand the difference and act appropriately where necessary. <br \/>\r\n<br \/>\r\nAnother factor a lot of sports, media &amp; entertainment companies have to consider is their licensing agreements. Counterfeiters often take advantage of these situations as they are not well monitored, but with the proper technology and strategy in place, brands can fight them off and make themselves a far more attractive partner for licensees to work with.<\/p>\n    <\/div>\n<\/section>\n\n<section class=\"industry-statistics\">\n    <div class=\"container\">\n        <h2 class=\"heading-branded\">Did you know?<\/h2>\n        <div class=\"statistics\">\n                        <div class=\"statistic\">\n                                <h4 class=\"statistic__figure brand--primary\">6.5%<\/h4>\n                <p>of all sporting trade in the EU is counterfeit<\/p>\n                            <\/div>\n                        <div class=\"statistic\">\n                                <h4 class=\"statistic__figure brand--primary\">2,800<\/h4>\n                <p>jobs are lost in the EU alone due to this issue<\/p>\n                            <\/div>\n                        <div class=\"statistic\">\n                                <h4 class=\"statistic__figure brand--primary\">3.3% <\/h4>\n                <p>of all global trade is suspected to be counterfeit<\/p>\n                            <\/div>\n                    <\/div>\n        <div class=\"approach\">\n            <div class=\"approach__inner\">\n                <div>\n                    <h3>How can Incopro Help?<\/h3>\n         